This paper deals with the mathematical framework for relating corresponding views in multiple view geometry, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision. The paper introduces a completion of bilinear maps between spaces given by an equivariant compactification of regular transformations, which is a mathematical concept that is commonly used in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with the extension of the completion to the varieties of fundamental and essential matrices, which involves linear algebra and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of algebraic geometry and topology, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GR (Computer Graphics). Finally, the paper involves numerical methods and optimization, which are relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
